The paper discusses the application of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) for EEG data analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper proposes the use of Layer-wise Relevance Propagation (LRP) to explain individual network decisions, which is a method commonly used in neural network interpretability research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses the potential of DNNs for investigating neural activity underlying complex perception or decision-related processes.
